{
  "text": "it's important to wait until the timer rings before trying these mushrooms otherwise you might start tripping out or you might see lots of weird colors today we're going to Tai Po Tian Fu Shan Zhen for a mushroom meal come on let's go eat some hotpot going through this menu is really really funny like listen to this one you would never expect this is a mushroom chilled black tiger feet wow chilled bigfoot mushrooms wow that really looks super meaty another interesting thing i am seeing about this menu is that you have all of the delicious vegetables and mushrooms right at the forefront of this menu and it's not even a vegetarian restaurant all of the meat is actually hidden at the back which is super curious but definitely my style and here even the tea is made from mushrooms look at that beautiful red color yes, it's a vegetarian dish, no chicken oil or mushroom soup it's a soup made from top-notch mushrooms what kind of sauce do you recommend? I recommend our special garlic and chili sauce because the chili sauce is home-made, it's not spicy so you have to eat it with the mushrooms okay one thing I really like about Tai Po is that you can order half portions so that means you can try so many more different types of mushrooms so it's important to wait until the timer rings before trying these mushrooms otherwise you might start tripping out like you're in san ti or three body problem with the numbers clocking down or you might see lots of weird colors just to be on the safe side I'm gonna wait until the timer's up the timer is up and the first thing we've been served is the soup base oh wow that is one of the most complex mushroom soups I've ever tasted that is so rich all right shall we go in for our first mushroom? the zhu sun or the bamboo mushroom wow that is soaking up so much broth let's dip it into our mushroom dipping sauce I think I know now why it's called a bamboo mushroom it actually has a very similar texture in the mouth to bamboo shoot a little bit crunchy, tender this mushroom has a very meaty name beef liver mushroom and it really looks like liver wow it definitely has a mushroom texture but it's super tender and I mean I haven't eaten liver in years but it does have that liver slipperiness that look to it for sure this is our scary mushroom the jian shou qing that if you eat it before it's ready you'll start to hallucinate so let's hope that I can finish this video without any hallucinations this mushroom gets its name because when it is exposed to air when raw it turns this vibrant blue shade here it's after being boiled it's turned more of a safe looking brown so I'm more comfortable eating it this way the mushroom is super tender it's almost like a mix between yam and a mushroom honestly it's very very subtle which is I think a good reason to have some of these dipping sauces here but we're not just eating mushrooms my favorite thing whenever I order hot pot is the fuzhu or bamboo style tofu skin and we also have the haozigar this is a Chinese favorite green for hot pot haozigar has a very particular flavor and it doesn't matter how strong the hot pot is that flavor will always shine through and I'm curious are there any other Chinese dishes that use haozigar because I've only ever seen it at hot pot places what I like to do towards the end of the meal is make my own mushroom noodle soup so we have our noodles in here the soup is going to be super fragrant because it's had all of those mushrooms and vegetables cooking up so just put in the noodles in there and let them cook for just a couple of minutes and then it will be ready bon appetit wow that is probably one of the best mushroom noodle soups I've ever had it's incredible all of those beautiful mushroom earthy flavors really make this mushroom soup broth stand out you really shouldn't miss out I'm Alex from Vegan in China see you next time bye bye",
